  • App Remote Control via Bluetooth 5.0ITC-312 Digital temperature controller has Bluetooth 5.0 that allows you to remotely control it through the INKBIRD app within 100 meters (328 feet)
  • Personalized mode settingsYou can set up to 12 periodic temperature ranges in a day using time mode. Two temperature ranges can be set in day/night mode. When in temperature mode, simply set the start and stop temperatures to run automatically
  • Reliable and Trustworthy with More FunctionsThis temperature controlled outlet features high and low temperature alarms, refrigeration delay protection, and temperature calibration
  • Waterproof Probe & Maximum Power OutputThe included temperature probe is IP67 waterproof and can accurately measure temperatures, temperature range: -40 to 212. Max power output: 1200W, which is shared between two different outlets
  • No Need to Store Data In the CloudTo prevent losing data, the ITC-312 device can store offline data for 30 days and transfer it to the INKBIRD app after connecting via Bluetooth. Moreover, the INKBIRD app can store 1 year temper data
  • Wide Application RangeThe ITC-312 Temperature Controller is useful for a range of temperature control needs including home living, heating, cultivation, seedling growing, and wooden sheds

        Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2024
        Arrived quickly and in perfect working order. I won't deduct stars for this as I was able to get the app to work. The directions say you need to sign into Inkbird.com or create an account. I went to their website and tried to create a new account as a... See more
        Arrived quickly and in perfect working order.

        I won't deduct stars for this as I was able to get the app to work.
        The directions say you need to sign into Inkbird.com or create an account. I went to their website and tried to create a new account as a new customer. There is a process you get a security code and you create a password. It would not accept the code and eventually have me a message: Sign in error with no code.

        I tried on Firefox, Opera, and Chrome all giving the same result. I mention this so Inkbird can fix this.

        The packaging is very nicely done.

        The device is very handsome looking.

        The sensor is permanently connected and the cabel feels very sturdy. The tip is stainless steel of good sturdy quality.

        The plug is 3 prong and also sturdy.

        The plugs have a small etched symbol for heat and cooling. These can be hard to see and tell what they are.

        Overall build quality is 5 stars.

        The directions that come with this do explain the button dial on the side a little. If you look under more product information you will find 2 PDF files one a manual and one for a more or less quick set up.

        The connection is easy overall.
        If you also can't make a Inkbird.com account on site.
        Download the Inkbird app. Create the account. It might tell you it has been made and when you try to sign in it says email or password are incorrect. Just hit forgot password and reenter your password, you get a pass code for security and enter it last then hit enter. It should say you're good.

        Now go back and enter the app. For some reasons this doesn't as farcas I know transfer to the site.

        One in the app it has to take several minutes or so to load and find your device. THIS CONNECTS USING THE APP not your Bluetooth list on your phone.

        Once the app loads images of all sorts of devices as long as yours is plugged in it wil show up automatically or at least mine did in a field above the other products.

        Just follow the onscreen directions.

        You should be connecting very soon after.

        The code the device starts with only goes away after you set things up.

        At the last step it shows it connecting and presto you're connected and the temperature appears.

        The app is straightforward and does what you would expect. It's a thermostat and settings app. Not a AAA game here.

      • Michael Coppola
        5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
        Just what I need and works great.
        Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2024
        So as the title says, this product is just what I need for precise temperature control in my fermentation fridge. It may or may not be just what you need for your particular application, so I would encourage everyone to read the specs carefully and make sure they're... See more
        So as the title says, this product is just what I need for precise temperature control in my fermentation fridge. It may or may not be just what you need for your particular application, so I would encourage everyone to read the specs carefully and make sure they're getting what they think they are before buying.

        Having said that, this controller works great for me. There are two modes for controlling temperature and I still haven't decided which one I like better. One mode works just like the older ITC-308 series where you set a target temperature and differentials for heating and cooling. In the other mode, you set start and stop temperatures for heating and cooling separately. There are also day/night and timed modes which I imagine might be very appealing to some users, but I haven't tried those because I don't think I'll ever need them.

        In any case, both temperature control modes can maintain my fermentation chamber within a very narrow range. At first I was rather conservative with it and set the heating and cooling three degrees fahrenheit apart, but eventually found that I can set them just one degree apart and it will maintain the temperature within a tenth of a degree above or below that range. Of course, I imagine that the specific heating and cooling units that you're using, as well as probe placement, might have an impact on this as well.

        The app was easy to download and install, and worked well for me once I played around with it a little to get a feel for it. The bluetooth range is pretty good in my house, but again this is probably something that will vary for different users. To me, it hasn't really mattered much because the controller keeps working even if it disconnects and stores temperature data that you can recover when you reconnect. Since I use my phone to run the app, it's always going to disconnect when I leave home, but it always reconnects when I return.

        The only negative for me is that I do wish that the temperature probe wasn't hard wired to the unit. Since I attach the probe to my fermenter inside the fridge, it would be nice to be able to disconnect the probe from the controller when I want to move things around instead of having to take it off the fermenter. But that's a pretty minor complaint so I'm still giving it five stars.

        I may come back and post an update after I use it some more.
